The paper proposes a novel approach to optimize the architecture of deep neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The approach is validated on image classification datasets, which suggests computer vision (cs.CV) as another likely sub-category. The use of mixed integer programming (MIP) formulation and optimization also suggests control and optimization (cs.SY) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with identifying critical neurons and removing non-critical ones, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE).
